00:45:31,264 --> 00:45:32,932
And nine millimeter Beretta.

793
00:45:33,867 --> 00:45:35,035
Oh and a Winchester.

794
00:45:36,403 --> 00:45:37,838
- A Winchester?

795
00:45:37,838 --> 00:45:39,006
That's an old west gun.

796
00:45:40,442 --> 00:45:42,744
- Always fancied meself a bit of a Calamity Jane,

797
00:45:42,744 --> 00:45:44,479
after I saw Doris Day in the movie.

798
00:45:46,148 --> 00:45:48,384
(laughing)

799
00:45:54,257 --> 00:45:55,425
- Where you from, Pete?

800
00:45:56,426 --> 00:45:57,929
- The Falls.

801
00:45:57,929 --> 00:45:59,630
- Aye, so am I.

802
00:46:00,898 --> 00:46:02,100
You look familiar to me.

803
00:46:08,107 --> 00:46:10,443
What do you know about guns?

804
00:46:11,611 --> 00:46:12,445
- Do you mind?

805
00:46:28,931 --> 00:46:30,333
- Why are you here?

806
00:46:31,968 --> 00:46:34,238
- I'm ready to kill, for you.

807
00:46:44,916 --> 00:46:46,352
- These are my people.

808
00:46:46,352 --> 00:46:47,453
Let me do the talking.

809
00:46:51,056 --> 00:46:53,660
(bluesy music)

810
00:46:59,834 --> 00:47:03,070
- What in the name of God in heaven are you doing here, son?

811
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:04,473
- I need to speak to Brian.

812
00:47:04,473 --> 00:47:05,707
Where can I find him?

813
00:47:05,707 --> 00:47:09,111
- If I was you, I'd be on my way.

814
00:47:09,111 --> 00:47:12,015
You've not many friends left around here.

815
00:47:12,015 --> 00:47:13,416
- What the bloody hell are you doing here, Johnny Fallon?

816
00:47:13,416 --> 00:47:15,418
- I'm not looking for trouble.

817
00:47:15,418 --> 00:47:17,521
I need to find Brian Fagen.

818
00:47:17,521 --> 00:47:19,223
Can anyone help me?

